entry.def: A fax or a fax machine is a piece of equipment used to copy documents by sending information electronically along a telephone line, and to receive copies that are sent in this way.

example.ex: ...a modern reception desk with telephone and fax...
example.tran: 有电话和传真机的现代化接待处

example.ex: These days, cartoonists send in their work by fax.
example.tran: 现在卡通画家用传真机发送作品。

entry.def: If you fax a document to someone, you send it from one fax machine to another.

example.ex: I faxed a copy of the agreement to each of the investors...
example.tran: 我给每个投资人都传真了一份合同。

example.ex: Did you fax him a reply?...

entry.def: You can refer to a copy of a document that is transmitted by a fax machine as a fax .

example.ex: I sent him a long fax, saying I didn't need a maid.
example.tran: 我给他发了一份很长的传真，说我不需要女仆。
